Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 08:18:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] interfaces: camera: fix undeclared F_DUPFD_CLOEXEC identifier

Android 12's standard library header cleanup removed implicit inclusions of `<fcntl.h>` in several Android framework headers. Because the legacy 1.0 Camera wrapper relies on `F_DUPFD_CLOEXEC`, compilation fails without the explicit `#include <fcntl.h>`. This patch adds the missing header.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Change-Id: If1c51a94f885c729046f719377d8aaf2e3bfd5d4
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp b/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp
index f324e45..360dedf 100644
--- a/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp
+++ b/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp
@@ -18,6 +18,7 @@
 #include <hardware/camera.h>
 #include <hardware/gralloc1.h>
 #include <hidlmemory/mapping.h>
+#include <fcntl.h>
 #include <log/log.h>
 #include <utils/Trace.h>
 
